g.text: This version aims to reduce the part count for easier DIY building. The 3 161's are replaced by a single 4040.

g.desc: This version aims to reduce the part count for easier DIY building. The 3 161's are replaced by a single 4040.

g.text: 161 clocks on rising edge and 4040 clocks on falling edge, so everything else also changes to work off active-high BLOCK & BYTE.

g.desc: 161 clocks on rising edge and 4040 clocks on falling edge, so everything else also changes to work off active-high BLOCK & BYTE.

g.text: 138 is replaced with 238, and 574 with 573. Being 256k-only vs 512k also saves a couple of other components.

g.desc: 138 is replaced with 238, and 574 with 573. Being 256k-only vs 512k also saves a couple of other components.

g.text: The 512k sram has no CE2 pin, so it would need to add a 2G02 (dual NOR) to invert RAMRST and then combine with BYTE to generate ~{CE}.

g.desc: The 512k sram has no CE2 pin, so it would need to add a 2G02 (dual NOR) to invert RAMRST and then combine with BYTE to generate ~{CE}.

g.text: 512k also needs a 9th bit of address latch, which would require adding a 1G373 to the 573.

g.desc: 512k also needs a 9th bit of address latch, which would require adding a 1G373 to the 573.
